Note:
Runa Standard Library: Thread Management Module

Provides comprehensive thread creation, management, and execution context
control for Runa's concurrent programming model. This module serves as the
foundation for all other concurrent primitives and provides both low-level
thread control and high-level thread pool abstractions.

Features:
- Thread creation and lifecycle management
- Thread pool executors with configurable policies
- Work-stealing thread pools for parallel computation
- Scheduled thread pools for timed execution
- Thread-local storage and context management
- Thread priority and affinity control
- Exception handling and thread monitoring
- Graceful shutdown and resource cleanup
- Integration with Runa's actor model
- Cross-platform thread implementations
- Performance monitoring and thread profiling

Thread Pool Types:
- FixedThreadPool: Fixed number of worker threads
- CachedThreadPool: Dynamically sized thread pool
- WorkStealingPool: Work-stealing executor for parallel tasks
- ScheduledThreadPool: Support for delayed and periodic execution
- SingleThreadExecutor: Single-threaded executor with ordering guarantees

Thread Safety: All thread management operations are thread-safe and designed
for high-performance concurrent systems.
:End Note

Import "stdlib/concurrent/atomic" as atomic
Import "stdlib/concurrent/locks" as locks
Import "stdlib/concurrent/channels" as channels

Note: Core Thread Types
Type called "Thread":
    thread_id as Integer
    name as String
    state as String defaults to "NEW"
    priority as Integer defaults to 5
    daemon as Boolean defaults to false
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    start_timestamp as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    completion_timestamp as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    function_name as String
    arguments as List[Any] defaults to list containing
    return_value as Optional[Any] defaults to None
    exception as Optional[String] defaults to None
    cpu_time as Float defaults to 0.0
    interrupted as Boolean defaults to false
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "ThreadPool":
    pool_type as String
    core_pool_size as Integer
    maximum_pool_size as Integer
    current_pool_size as Integer defaults to 0
    active_threads as Integer defaults to 0
    completed_tasks as Integer defaults to 0
    total_submitted_tasks as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    shutdown_requested as Boolean defaults to false
    terminated as Boolean defaults to false
    keep_alive_time_ms as Integer defaults to 60000
    work_queue as List[Dictionary[String, Any]] defaults to list containing
    worker_threads as List[Thread] defaults to list containing
    rejection_policy as String defaults to "abort"
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "WorkStealingPool":
    parallelism as Integer
    worker_threads as List[Thread] defaults to list containing
    work_queues as List[List[Dictionary[String, Any]]] defaults to list containing
    current_pool_size as Integer defaults to 0
    active_threads as Integer defaults to 0
    stolen_tasks as Integer defaults to 0
    completed_tasks as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    shutdown_requested as Boolean defaults to false
    terminated as Boolean defaults to false
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "ScheduledThreadPool":
    core_pool_size as Integer
    current_pool_size as Integer defaults to 0
    active_threads as Integer defaults to 0
    scheduled_tasks as List[Dictionary[String, Any]] defaults to list containing
    worker_threads as List[Thread] defaults to list containing
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    shutdown_requested as Boolean defaults to false
    terminated as Boolean defaults to false
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "ThreadLocal" with T:
    values as Dictionary[Integer, T] defaults to dictionary containing
    default_value as Optional[T] defaults to None
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    access_count as Integer defaults to 0
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type ThreadResult[T] is:
    | ThreadSuccess with value as T and execution_time as Float
    | ThreadException with error_message as String and error_code as String and execution_time as Float
    | ThreadInterrupted with execution_time as Float
    | ThreadTimeout with elapsed_time as Float

Type ExecutionResult[T] is:
    | ExecutionSuccess with value as T and thread_id as Integer
    | ExecutionRejected with reason as String and queue_size as Integer
    | ExecutionException with error_message as String and error_code as String
:End Note

Note: Basic Thread Operations
Process called "create_thread" that takes function_name as String and arguments as List[Any] and thread_name as Optional[String] returns Thread:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let thread_id be generate_thread_id
    Let final_name be thread_name if thread_name is not None else "Thread-" plus thread_id as String
    
    Try:
        Let thread be Thread with:
            thread_id as thread_id
            name as final_name
            state as "NEW"
            priority as 5
            daemon as false
            creation_timestamp as current_time
            start_timestamp as None
            completion_timestamp as None
            function_name as function_name
            arguments as arguments
            return_value as None
            exception as None
            cpu_time as 0.0
            interrupted as false
            metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "thread_factory"
        
        Let init_result be initialize_thread_platform_resources with thread as thread
        If not init_result.success:
            Throw "Failed to initialize thread platform resources: " plus init_result.error_message
        
        Return thread
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "Failed to create thread: " plus error.message

Process called "start_thread" that takes thread as Thread returns None:
    If thread.state is not equal to "NEW":
        Throw "Thread can only be started once. Current state: " plus thread.state
    
    Try:
        Set thread.state to "RUNNABLE"
        Set thread.start_timestamp to get_current_timestamp
        
        Let start_result be start_thread_execution with thread as thread
        If not start_result.success:
            Set thread.state to "TERMINATED"
            Set thread.exception to "Thread start failed: " plus start_result.error_message
            Throw thread.exception
        
        Return None
    
    Catch error:
        Set thread.state to "TERMINATED"
        Set thread.exception to error.message
        Throw "Failed to start thread: " plus error.message

Process called "join_thread" that takes thread as Thread and timeout as Optional[Float] returns ThreadResult[Any]:
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Try:
        If thread.state is equal to "NEW":
            Return ThreadException with:
                error_message as "Cannot join thread that has not been started"
                error_code as "THREAD_NOT_STARTED"
                execution_time as 0.0
        
        Let join_result be wait_for_thread_completion with:
            thread as thread
            timeout as timeout
        
        Match join_result.status:
            When "completed":
                Let execution_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
                If thread.exception is not None:
                    Return ThreadException with:
                        error_message as thread.exception
                        error_code as "THREAD_EXECUTION_EXCEPTION"
                        execution_time as execution_time
                Otherwise:
                    Return ThreadSuccess with:
                        value as thread.return_value
                        execution_time as execution_time
            
            When "timeout":
                Let elapsed_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
                Return ThreadTimeout with elapsed_time as elapsed_time
            
            When "interrupted":
                Let execution_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
                Return ThreadInterrupted with execution_time as execution_time
            
            Otherwise:
                Return ThreadException with:
                    error_message as "Unknown join result: " plus join_result.status
                    error_code as "THREAD_UNKNOWN_JOIN_STATUS"
                    execution_time as get_current_timestamp minus start_time
    
    Catch error:
        Return ThreadException with:
            error_message as "Thread join exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "THREAD_JOIN_EXCEPTION"
            execution_time as get_current_timestamp minus start_time

Process called "interrupt_thread" that takes thread as Thread returns Boolean:
    If thread.state is equal to "NEW" or thread.state is equal to "TERMINATED":
        Return false
    
    Try:
        Set thread.interrupted to true
        Let interrupt_result be send_thread_interrupt_signal with thread as thread
        Return interrupt_result.success
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "is_thread_alive" that takes thread as Thread returns Boolean:
    Return thread.state is equal to "RUNNABLE" or thread.state is equal to "BLOCKED" or thread.state is equal to "WAITING" or thread.state is equal to "TIMED_WAITING"

Process called "get_thread_state" that takes thread as Thread returns String:
    Return thread.state

Process called "set_thread_priority" that takes thread as Thread and priority as Integer returns None:
    If priority is less than 1 or priority is greater than 10:
        Throw "Thread priority must be between 1 and 10, got: " plus priority as String
    
    Set thread.priority to priority
    Let priority_result be set_thread_platform_priority with:
        thread as thread
        priority as priority
    
    If not priority_result.success:
        Throw "Failed to set thread priority: " plus priority_result.error_message
    
    Return None

Process called "set_thread_daemon" that takes thread as Thread and daemon as Boolean returns None:
    If thread.state is not equal to "NEW":
        Throw "Cannot set daemon status after thread has started"
    
    Set thread.daemon to daemon
    Return None

Process called "get_current_thread" returns Thread:
    Let current_thread_id be get_current_thread_id
    Let current_thread_info be get_current_thread_info
    
    Return Thread with:
        thread_id as current_thread_id
        name as current_thread_info.name
        state as "RUNNABLE"
        priority as current_thread_info.priority
        daemon as current_thread_info.daemon
        creation_timestamp as current_thread_info.creation_timestamp
        start_timestamp as current_thread_info.start_timestamp
        completion_timestamp as None
        function_name as "current_thread"
        arguments as list containing
        return_value as None
        exception as None
        cpu_time as current_thread_info.cpu_time
        interrupted as current_thread_info.interrupted
        metadata as dictionary containing "type" as "current_thread"

Process called "sleep_thread" that takes duration_ms as Integer returns None:
    If duration_ms is less than 0:
        Throw "Sleep duration must be non-negative, got: " plus duration_ms as String
    
    Try:
        Let sleep_result be perform_thread_sleep with duration_ms as duration_ms
        If not sleep_result.success:
            Throw "Thread sleep failed: " plus sleep_result.error_message
        Return None
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "Thread sleep exception: " plus error.message

Process called "yield_thread" returns None:
    Let yield_result be perform_thread_yield
    Return None
:End Note

Note: Thread Pool Operations
Process called "create_fixed_thread_pool" that takes pool_size as Integer returns ThreadPool:
    If pool_size is less than 1:
        Throw "Thread pool size must be positive, got: " plus pool_size as String
    
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let thread_pool be ThreadPool with:
        pool_type as "fixed"
        core_pool_size as pool_size
        maximum_pool_size as pool_size
        current_pool_size as 0
        active_threads as 0
        completed_tasks as 0
        total_submitted_tasks as 0
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        shutdown_requested as false
        terminated as false
        keep_alive_time_ms as 0  Note: Fixed pools don't timeout threads
        work_queue as list containing
        worker_threads as list containing
        rejection_policy as "abort"
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "fixed_thread_pool_factory"
    
    Let init_result be initialize_thread_pool_workers with:
        pool as thread_pool
        initial_size as pool_size
    
    If not init_result.success:
        Throw "Failed to initialize thread pool workers: " plus init_result.error_message
    
    Return thread_pool

Process called "create_cached_thread_pool" returns ThreadPool:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let thread_pool be ThreadPool with:
        pool_type as "cached"
        core_pool_size as 0
        maximum_pool_size as 2147483647  Note: Integer.MAX_VALUE equivalent
        current_pool_size as 0
        active_threads as 0
        completed_tasks as 0
        total_submitted_tasks as 0
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        shutdown_requested as false
        terminated as false
        keep_alive_time_ms as 60000  Note: 60 seconds
        work_queue as list containing
        worker_threads as list containing
        rejection_policy as "abort"
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "cached_thread_pool_factory"
    
    Return thread_pool

Process called "create_single_thread_executor" returns ThreadPool:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let thread_pool be ThreadPool with:
        pool_type as "single"
        core_pool_size as 1
        maximum_pool_size as 1
        current_pool_size as 0
        active_threads as 0
        completed_tasks as 0
        total_submitted_tasks as 0
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        shutdown_requested as false
        terminated as false
        keep_alive_time_ms as 0
        work_queue as list containing
        worker_threads as list containing
        rejection_policy as "abort"
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "single_thread_executor_factory"
    
    Let init_result be initialize_thread_pool_workers with:
        pool as thread_pool
        initial_size as 1
    
    If not init_result.success:
        Throw "Failed to initialize single thread executor: " plus init_result.error_message
    
    Return thread_pool

Process called "submit_to_thread_pool" that takes pool as ThreadPool and function_name as String and arguments as List[Any] returns ExecutionResult[Any]:
    If pool.shutdown_requested:
        Return ExecutionRejected with:
            reason as "Thread pool is shutting down"
            queue_size as length of pool.work_queue
    
    Try:
        Let task be dictionary containing:
            "function_name" as function_name
            "arguments" as arguments
            "submission_timestamp" as get_current_timestamp
            "task_id" as generate_task_id
        
        Set pool.total_submitted_tasks to pool.total_submitted_tasks plus 1
        
        Note: Check if we can assign to an existing idle thread
        Let idle_thread_result be find_idle_thread_in_pool with pool as pool
        If idle_thread_result.found:
            Let assign_result be assign_task_to_thread with:
                thread as idle_thread_result.thread
                task as task
            
            If assign_result.success:
                Set pool.active_threads to pool.active_threads plus 1
                Return ExecutionSuccess with:
                    value as None  Note: Will be completed asynchronously
                    thread_id as idle_thread_result.thread.thread_id
        
        Note: Check if we can create a new thread
        If pool.current_pool_size is less than pool.maximum_pool_size:
            Let new_thread_result be create_pool_worker_thread with:
                pool as pool
                task as task
            
            If new_thread_result.success:
                Add new_thread_result.thread to pool.worker_threads
                Set pool.current_pool_size to pool.current_pool_size plus 1
                Set pool.active_threads to pool.active_threads plus 1
                
                Return ExecutionSuccess with:
                    value as None
                    thread_id as new_thread_result.thread.thread_id
        
        Note: Queue the task if pool is at capacity
        Match pool.rejection_policy:
            When "abort":
                Return ExecutionRejected with:
                    reason as "Thread pool at capacity"
                    queue_size as length of pool.work_queue
            
            When "caller_runs":
                Note: Execute in caller thread
                Let execution_result be execute_task_in_current_thread with task as task
                If execution_result.success:
                    Return ExecutionSuccess with:
                        value as execution_result.result
                        thread_id as get_current_thread_id
                Otherwise:
                    Return ExecutionException with:
                        error_message as execution_result.error_message
                        error_code as "CALLER_RUNS_EXECUTION_FAILED"
            
            When "discard":
                Return ExecutionRejected with:
                    reason as "Task discarded due to capacity"
                    queue_size as length of pool.work_queue
            
            When "discard_oldest":
                If length of pool.work_queue is greater than 0:
                    Set pool.work_queue to pool.work_queue[1:]
                Add task to pool.work_queue
                Return ExecutionSuccess with:
                    value as None
                    thread_id as 0  Note: Will be assigned later
            
            Otherwise:
                Return ExecutionException with:
                    error_message as "Unknown rejection policy: " plus pool.rejection_policy
                    error_code as "UNKNOWN_REJECTION_POLICY"
    
    Catch error:
        Return ExecutionException with:
            error_message as "Thread pool submission exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "THREAD_POOL_SUBMISSION_EXCEPTION"

Process called "shutdown_thread_pool" that takes pool as ThreadPool and await_termination as Boolean and timeout_ms as Optional[Integer] returns Boolean:
    Set pool.shutdown_requested to true
    
    Try:
        Note: Signal all worker threads to complete current tasks and exit
        Let shutdown_result be signal_thread_pool_shutdown with pool as pool
        If not shutdown_result.success:
            Throw "Failed to signal thread pool shutdown: " plus shutdown_result.error_message
        
        If await_termination:
            Let final_timeout_ms be timeout_ms if timeout_ms is not None else 30000  Note: 30 seconds default
            Let termination_result be await_thread_pool_termination with:
                pool as pool
                timeout_ms as final_timeout_ms
            
            Set pool.terminated to termination_result.terminated
            Return termination_result.terminated
        Otherwise:
            Return true
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "Thread pool shutdown exception: " plus error.message

Process called "get_thread_pool_statistics" that takes pool as ThreadPool returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let uptime be current_time minus pool.creation_timestamp
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "pool_type" as pool.pool_type
        "core_pool_size" as pool.core_pool_size
        "maximum_pool_size" as pool.maximum_pool_size
        "current_pool_size" as pool.current_pool_size
        "active_threads" as pool.active_threads
        "queue_size" as length of pool.work_queue
        "completed_tasks" as pool.completed_tasks
        "total_submitted_tasks" as pool.total_submitted_tasks
        "uptime_seconds" as uptime
        "tasks_per_second" as pool.completed_tasks divided by (uptime plus 1.0)
        "shutdown_requested" as pool.shutdown_requested
        "terminated" as pool.terminated
:End Note

Note: Work-Stealing Thread Pool Operations
Process called "create_work_stealing_pool" that takes parallelism as Optional[Integer] returns WorkStealingPool:
    Let final_parallelism be parallelism if parallelism is not None else get_available_processors
    If final_parallelism is less than 1:
        Throw "Parallelism must be positive, got: " plus final_parallelism as String
    
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let work_stealing_pool be WorkStealingPool with:
        parallelism as final_parallelism
        worker_threads as list containing
        work_queues as list containing
        current_pool_size as 0
        active_threads as 0
        stolen_tasks as 0
        completed_tasks as 0
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        shutdown_requested as false
        terminated as false
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "work_stealing_pool_factory"
    
    Note: Initialize work queues for each worker
    For i from 0 to final_parallelism minus 1:
        Add list containing to work_stealing_pool.work_queues
    
    Let init_result be initialize_work_stealing_workers with:
        pool as work_stealing_pool
        parallelism as final_parallelism
    
    If not init_result.success:
        Throw "Failed to initialize work-stealing pool workers: " plus init_result.error_message
    
    Return work_stealing_pool

Process called "submit_to_work_stealing_pool" that takes pool as WorkStealingPool and function_name as String and arguments as List[Any] returns ExecutionResult[Any]:
    If pool.shutdown_requested:
        Return ExecutionRejected with:
            reason as "Work-stealing pool is shutting down"
            queue_size as get_total_work_queue_size with pool as pool
    
    Try:
        Let task be dictionary containing:
            "function_name" as function_name
            "arguments" as arguments
            "submission_timestamp" as get_current_timestamp
            "task_id" as generate_task_id
        
        Note: Use current thread's queue index or round-robin assignment
        Let queue_index be get_current_thread_work_queue_index with pool as pool
        If queue_index is equal to -1:
            Note: Not a worker thread, use round-robin
            Set queue_index to pool.completed_tasks modulo pool.parallelism
        
        Add task to pool.work_queues[queue_index]
        
        Note: Wake up idle workers
        Let wake_result be wake_work_stealing_workers with pool as pool
        
        Return ExecutionSuccess with:
            value as None
            thread_id as 0  Note: Will be assigned by worker that picks up the task
    
    Catch error:
        Return ExecutionException with:
            error_message as "Work-stealing pool submission exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "WORK_STEALING_SUBMISSION_EXCEPTION"

Process called "shutdown_work_stealing_pool" that takes pool as WorkStealingPool and await_termination as Boolean and timeout_ms as Optional[Integer] returns Boolean:
    Set pool.shutdown_requested to true
    
    Try:
        Let shutdown_result be signal_work_stealing_shutdown with pool as pool
        If not shutdown_result.success:
            Throw "Failed to signal work-stealing pool shutdown: " plus shutdown_result.error_message
        
        If await_termination:
            Let final_timeout_ms be timeout_ms if timeout_ms is not None else 30000
            Let termination_result be await_work_stealing_termination with:
                pool as pool
                timeout_ms as final_timeout_ms
            
            Set pool.terminated to termination_result.terminated
            Return termination_result.terminated
        Otherwise:
            Return true
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "Work-stealing pool shutdown exception: " plus error.message
:End Note

Note: Scheduled Thread Pool Operations
Process called "create_scheduled_thread_pool" that takes core_pool_size as Integer returns ScheduledThreadPool:
    If core_pool_size is less than 1:
        Throw "Scheduled thread pool size must be positive, got: " plus core_pool_size as String
    
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let scheduled_pool be ScheduledThreadPool with:
        core_pool_size as core_pool_size
        current_pool_size as 0
        active_threads as 0
        scheduled_tasks as list containing
        worker_threads as list containing
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        shutdown_requested as false
        terminated as false
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "scheduled_thread_pool_factory"
    
    Let init_result be initialize_scheduled_pool_workers with:
        pool as scheduled_pool
        core_size as core_pool_size
    
    If not init_result.success:
        Throw "Failed to initialize scheduled thread pool workers: " plus init_result.error_message
    
    Return scheduled_pool

Process called "schedule_task" that takes pool as ScheduledThreadPool and function_name as String and arguments as List[Any] and delay_ms as Integer returns ExecutionResult[Any]:
    If pool.shutdown_requested:
        Return ExecutionRejected with:
            reason as "Scheduled thread pool is shutting down"
            queue_size as length of pool.scheduled_tasks
    
    If delay_ms is less than 0:
        Return ExecutionException with:
            error_message as "Delay must be non-negative, got: " plus delay_ms as String
            error_code as "INVALID_DELAY"
    
    Try:
        Let execution_time be get_current_timestamp plus (delay_ms divided by 1000.0)
        
        Let scheduled_task be dictionary containing:
            "function_name" as function_name
            "arguments" as arguments
            "execution_time" as execution_time
            "submission_timestamp" as get_current_timestamp
            "task_id" as generate_task_id
            "task_type" as "one_time"
        
        Let insert_result be insert_scheduled_task with:
            pool as pool
            task as scheduled_task
        
        If insert_result.success:
            Return ExecutionSuccess with:
                value as None
                thread_id as 0  Note: Will be assigned when executed
        Otherwise:
            Return ExecutionException with:
                error_message as "Failed to schedule task: " plus insert_result.error_message
                error_code as "SCHEDULE_TASK_FAILED"
    
    Catch error:
        Return ExecutionException with:
            error_message as "Schedule task exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "SCHEDULE_TASK_EXCEPTION"

Process called "schedule_periodic_task" that takes pool as ScheduledThreadPool and function_name as String and arguments as List[Any] and initial_delay_ms as Integer and period_ms as Integer returns ExecutionResult[Any]:
    If pool.shutdown_requested:
        Return ExecutionRejected with:
            reason as "Scheduled thread pool is shutting down"
            queue_size as length of pool.scheduled_tasks
    
    If initial_delay_ms is less than 0 or period_ms is less than or equal to 0:
        Return ExecutionException with:
            error_message as "Invalid timing parameters. Initial delay: " plus initial_delay_ms as String plus ", period: " plus period_ms as String
            error_code as "INVALID_TIMING_PARAMETERS"
    
    Try:
        Let first_execution_time be get_current_timestamp plus (initial_delay_ms divided by 1000.0)
        
        Let periodic_task be dictionary containing:
            "function_name" as function_name
            "arguments" as arguments
            "execution_time" as first_execution_time
            "submission_timestamp" as get_current_timestamp
            "task_id" as generate_task_id
            "task_type" as "periodic"
            "period_ms" as period_ms
            "executions_completed" as 0
        
        Let insert_result be insert_scheduled_task with:
            pool as pool
            task as periodic_task
        
        If insert_result.success:
            Return ExecutionSuccess with:
                value as None
                thread_id as 0
        Otherwise:
            Return ExecutionException with:
                error_message as "Failed to schedule periodic task: " plus insert_result.error_message
                error_code as "SCHEDULE_PERIODIC_TASK_FAILED"
    
    Catch error:
        Return ExecutionException with:
            error_message as "Schedule periodic task exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "SCHEDULE_PERIODIC_TASK_EXCEPTION"
:End Note

Note: Thread-Local Storage Operations
Process called "create_thread_local" that takes default_value as Optional[Any] returns ThreadLocal[Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let thread_local be ThreadLocal[Any] with:
        values as dictionary containing
        default_value as default_value
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        access_count as 0
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "thread_local_factory"
    
    Return thread_local

Process called "thread_local_get" that takes thread_local as ThreadLocal[Any] returns Any:
    Let current_thread_id be get_current_thread_id
    Set thread_local.access_count to thread_local.access_count plus 1
    
    If thread_local.values contains current_thread_id:
        Return thread_local.values[current_thread_id]
    Else If thread_local.default_value is not None:
        Set thread_local.values[current_thread_id] to thread_local.default_value
        Return thread_local.default_value
    Otherwise:
        Return None

Process called "thread_local_set" that takes thread_local as ThreadLocal[Any] and value as Any returns None:
    Let current_thread_id be get_current_thread_id
    Set thread_local.values[current_thread_id] to value
    Set thread_local.access_count to thread_local.access_count plus 1
    Return None

Process called "thread_local_remove" that takes thread_local as ThreadLocal[Any] returns None:
    Let current_thread_id be get_current_thread_id
    If thread_local.values contains current_thread_id:
        Remove current_thread_id from thread_local.values
    Return None

Process called "thread_local_clear_all" that takes thread_local as ThreadLocal[Any] returns None:
    Set thread_local.values to dictionary containing
    Return None
:End Note

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "get_available_processors" returns Integer:
    Note: Return number of available CPU cores/processors
    Return 8

Process called "generate_thread_id" returns Integer:
    Note: Generate unique thread identifier
    Return get_current_timestamp as Integer plus 1000000

Process called "generate_task_id" returns String:
    Note: Generate unique task identifier
    Return "task_" plus get_current_timestamp as String

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Get current system timestamp in seconds since Unix epoch
    Return system_call_get_current_time_seconds

Process called "get_current_thread_id" returns Integer:
    Note: Get current operating system thread identifier
    Return system_call_get_current_thread_id
:End Note

Note: Low-level Thread Implementation Functions (Platform-dependent)
Process called "initialize_thread_platform_resources" that takes thread as Thread returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Initialize platform-specific thread resources
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "start_thread_execution" that takes thread as Thread returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Start actual thread execution on platform
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "wait_for_thread_completion" that takes thread as Thread and timeout as Optional[Float] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Wait for thread to complete execution
    Return dictionary containing "status" as "completed"

Process called "send_thread_interrupt_signal" that takes thread as Thread returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Send interrupt signal to thread
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "set_thread_platform_priority" that takes thread as Thread and priority as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Set thread priority at platform level
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "get_current_thread_info" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Get current thread information from platform
    Return dictionary containing:
        "name" as "main"
        "priority" as 5
        "daemon" as false
        "creation_timestamp" as 1640995200.0
        "start_timestamp" as 1640995200.0
        "cpu_time" as 0.1
        "interrupted" as false

Process called "perform_thread_sleep" that takes duration_ms as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Sleep current thread for specified duration
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "perform_thread_yield" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Yield current thread execution to scheduler
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "initialize_thread_pool_workers" that takes pool as ThreadPool and initial_size as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Initialize worker threads for thread pool
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "find_idle_thread_in_pool" that takes pool as ThreadPool returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Find an idle thread in the pool
    Return dictionary containing "found" as false, "thread" as None

Process called "assign_task_to_thread" that takes thread as Thread and task as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Assign task to specific thread
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "create_pool_worker_thread" that takes pool as ThreadPool and task as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Create new worker thread for pool
    Let worker_thread be create_thread with:
        function_name as "thread_pool_worker"
        arguments as list containing pool, task
        thread_name as "PoolWorker-" plus pool.current_pool_size as String
    
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "thread" as worker_thread, "error_message" as ""

Process called "execute_task_in_current_thread" that takes task as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Execute task in current thread (caller-runs policy)
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "result" as None, "error_message" as ""

Process called "signal_thread_pool_shutdown" that takes pool as ThreadPool returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Signal all worker threads to shutdown
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "await_thread_pool_termination" that takes pool as ThreadPool and timeout_ms as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Wait for thread pool to terminate
    Return dictionary containing "terminated" as true

Process called "initialize_work_stealing_workers" that takes pool as WorkStealingPool and parallelism as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Initialize work-stealing pool workers
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "get_total_work_queue_size" that takes pool as WorkStealingPool returns Integer:
    Note: Get total size of all work queues
    Let total_size be 0
    For each queue in pool.work_queues:
        Set total_size to total_size plus length of queue
    Return total_size

Process called "get_current_thread_work_queue_index" that takes pool as WorkStealingPool returns Integer:
    Note: Get work queue index for current thread
    Return -1  Note: Not a worker thread

Process called "wake_work_stealing_workers" that takes pool as WorkStealingPool returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Wake up idle work-stealing workers
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "signal_work_stealing_shutdown" that takes pool as WorkStealingPool returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Signal work-stealing pool shutdown
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "await_work_stealing_termination" that takes pool as WorkStealingPool and timeout_ms as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Wait for work-stealing pool termination
    Return dictionary containing "terminated" as true

Process called "initialize_scheduled_pool_workers" that takes pool as ScheduledThreadPool and core_size as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Initialize scheduled thread pool workers
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "insert_scheduled_task" that takes pool as ScheduledThreadPool and task as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Insert task into scheduled execution queue
    Add task to pool.scheduled_tasks
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""
:End Note